WEBVTT

01:13.314 --> 01:14.235
Hey, welcome, Concord.

01:14.355 --> 01:14.936
Glad you're here.

01:15.296 --> 01:23.264
For those who are here in Claremont and those who are joining us online and at all our campuses, and we pray today that God will do a great work Concord.

01:23.305 --> 01:26.248
I'm Derek, I haven't met you yet, and glad to see you this morning.

01:27.449 --> 01:34.216
Today is family worship, and one of the things I want to do, my family is in Dacula every Sunday morning, so you don't get to meet them, and so I brought a picture.

01:34.316 --> 01:37.439
I want to show you guys that real quick and introduce our family.

01:37.980 --> 01:39.922
If you haven't met them, if you haven't already,

01:40.130 --> 01:43.075
But come on friends, social media, and check out my family's photos.

01:43.115 --> 01:43.696
So here they are.

01:44.076 --> 01:45.559
So Grant is our oldest son.

01:45.599 --> 01:47.682
He's 21 years old at the University of Georgia.

01:48.143 --> 01:52.289
Emma Grace, our daughter, is 15, and she is a sophomore at the Kiel High School.

01:52.630 --> 01:55.074
My wife, Kim, we've been married 25 years this summer.

01:55.715 --> 01:56.616
Andy is 18.

01:56.656 --> 01:59.801
I just graduated from the Kiel High School, working as a landscaper right now.

02:00.342 --> 02:08.114
And then me, and then everybody's favorite, PJ, or as we affectionately know him, and all the kids know him as PJ, the three-legged wonder dog.

02:08.194 --> 02:09.175
P.J.

02:09.235 --> 02:10.637
is awesome, and he really does.

02:10.717 --> 02:13.740
Two front, one back, and he can run with the best of them.

02:13.760 --> 02:18.526
And especially when I get around little kids, man, we'll take him out into a field, and the kids will always say, can P.J.

02:18.606 --> 02:20.428
run with me, and man, we run, and we have a good time.

02:20.828 --> 02:27.396
But I want you to see our family, and know who we are, and so they can't be here on Sundays, but glad you all are here.

02:27.936 --> 02:30.980
Take your Bible, please, and turn to Ephesians chapter 6, verse 18.

02:31.620 --> 02:32.842
Ephesians 6, 18.

02:32.862 --> 02:36.626
You know, at Concord, we say that we

02:36.898 --> 02:41.044
believe that God through His word clearly says that we are to make disciples everywhere.

02:41.664 --> 02:42.766
Make disciples everywhere.

02:42.786 --> 02:50.336
And of course, as we're making disciples, that includes the way we serve people, the way we live for Christ, the way we invite people to church, the way we pray with people.

02:50.376 --> 02:58.047
But one thing I want us to focus in on today is this, undergirding everything that we do is prayer.

02:58.767 --> 03:02.212
And I want us to look because God's word teaches us how to pray.

03:02.292 --> 03:06.578
Jesus shows us, He models it, He shows us, but I want us to talk about this morning.

03:06.914 --> 03:14.265
what God teaches us in His Word and His passage in a couple of verses about seven ways to pray evangelistically.

03:15.507 --> 03:22.979
My prayer is that this might even be just a great day for each of us that God would encourage us and convict us about our prayer lives.

03:23.640 --> 03:26.204
Seven ways to pray evangelistically.

03:26.785 --> 03:32.914
The Apostle Paul in this passage writing to us was in prison for sharing the gospel.

03:33.218 --> 03:39.346
The reason he was in prison was because it was illegal in the Roman government to stand up and to say, Jesus is Lord.

03:39.887 --> 03:48.177
So as they were sorting things out, figuring out what was gonna come with Paul, Paul was writing, and he was writing to the people there, and he was writing to us.

03:48.237 --> 03:52.923
And so Paul, in Ephesians chapter six, we're gonna read three verses, starting in verse 18.

03:52.943 --> 03:55.006
Would you stand with me, please, for the reading of God's Word?

03:55.687 --> 04:01.234
Ephesians six, verse 18, and following says, pray it all times in the spirit.

04:01.890 --> 04:07.016
with every prayer and request, and stay alert with all perseverance and intercession for all the saints.

04:07.877 --> 04:14.786
Pray also for me that the message may be given to me when I open my mouth to make known with boldness the mystery of the gospel.

04:15.587 --> 04:18.350
For this, I am an ambassador in chains.

04:19.011 --> 04:23.176
Pray that I might be bold enough to speak about it as I should.

04:23.516 --> 04:24.077
Let's pray together.

04:24.578 --> 04:28.803
We do pray, God, through your word, through your Holy Spirit, you will speak to each of us today.

04:29.604 --> 04:31.346
Lord, speak to us about prayer,

04:31.682 --> 04:46.097
about the power of it and how to pray and Father compel us to be, as your people, to be about the business of prayer day in and day out, Father, so that we will do our part through prayer in the loss coming to faith in Christ.

04:46.478 --> 04:49.401
And so Father, thank you for Concord, thank you for all that you're doing here.

04:50.402 --> 04:55.988
Thank you Father for the new members who are being added to the church and God people who are coming to faith in Christ.

04:56.328 --> 05:01.554
And we pray that we continue and we do pray today right now that you speak to us through your word

05:01.698 --> 05:04.041
Your spirit is in Jesus and we pray.

05:04.442 --> 05:04.742
Amen.

05:05.303 --> 05:05.944
Please be seated.

05:06.445 --> 05:12.954
So I was a freshman in high school playing football and that year our team ended the season 0 and 10.

05:13.595 --> 05:17.180
I don't know if you've ever played on a totally defeated team before, but it ain't no fun.

05:17.500 --> 05:18.361
I mean, it was awful.

05:19.123 --> 05:20.505
The next year we improved a little bit.

05:20.525 --> 05:21.586
We were three and seven.

05:22.594 --> 05:27.701
The following year, we had some younger guys that were good players that came in as freshmen.

05:28.322 --> 05:31.566
We had an older group, us, Jews and seniors that were sort of jelling together.

05:32.467 --> 05:36.272
We had some coaches who figured out a new offense that would help us.

05:36.793 --> 05:39.837
And also, there were some spiritual things that happened that year.

05:40.478 --> 05:46.165
Before every gain, we had a chaplain and he was a very godly man and he would come and he would give a devotion.

05:46.666 --> 05:49.650
And then after the devotion, we would all say the Lord's prayer together.

05:50.594 --> 05:56.425
But it was a group of us, about eight of us on the first week that, man, God was really doing a great work in our life.

05:56.505 --> 06:09.368
As a matter of fact, you may remember when I shared my testimony a couple of weeks ago that, man, God just gave me and other guys and young ladies that were classmates, a passion to see our friends and our classmates come to faith in Christ.

06:09.428 --> 06:13.716
So, man, we were humbly but bold living for Jesus all through high school.

06:13.776 --> 06:14.898
We even started and

06:15.074 --> 06:24.284
on-campus Bible study, our sophomore year, and then our junior year, we actually started a fellowship of Christian athletes, and Steve Parr was our very first sponsor that helped.

06:24.324 --> 06:31.111
So I was a high school student, and Steve was a youth pastor at Hebrew at the time, and we started this fellowship of Christian athletes together.

06:31.131 --> 06:42.002
So it was that same year that these eight of us had a desire to pray together before the game, and now we didn't pray, God help us win.

06:43.042 --> 06:43.322
Right?

06:43.503 --> 06:45.525
I mean, you know, that's how some people pray for games.

06:45.545 --> 06:48.409
You know, they want Clemson to beat Georgia Tech or the other way around.

06:48.429 --> 06:50.271
They want the dogs to beat Vandy or whatever.

06:51.613 --> 06:54.897
But we at least had the maturity to pray.

06:54.977 --> 06:58.822
God, help us to play together as a team and to play well well.

06:59.222 --> 07:00.283
Help us to be safe.

07:00.844 --> 07:02.806
Help us to play in a way that would honor you.

07:02.907 --> 07:05.310
Help us to do our best, you know, everything we do.

07:06.030 --> 07:10.476
And lo and behold, put all these factors together and we started winning games.

07:10.516 --> 07:12.178
By the time we got to week seven,

07:12.578 --> 07:13.439
We're seven and oh.

07:14.281 --> 07:17.706
And that prayer group of eight people had grown.

07:18.507 --> 07:19.689
About half the team was praying.

07:19.709 --> 07:21.592
I mean, ball players are superstitious.

07:21.973 --> 07:23.796
And if something's working, they're gonna do it.

07:24.517 --> 07:27.201
So if people are, I mean, if we're winning, they're gonna join the prayer.

07:27.221 --> 07:28.283
But God used that.

07:28.303 --> 07:31.287
As a matter of fact, I remember one guy in particular and there's no joke.

07:31.307 --> 07:34.612
He was one of our offensive tackles and he was not a believer yet.

07:35.514 --> 07:40.722
And we would go around and whoever wanted to pray could pray or just skip you or whatever if you didn't want to pray.

07:40.930 --> 07:43.914
But I remember he literally prayed this, dear God, thank you, amen.

07:44.835 --> 07:45.216
That was it.

07:45.336 --> 07:46.057
That's why he prayed.

07:46.738 --> 07:47.579
But it was awesome, right?

07:47.599 --> 07:51.565
He was talking to God and God was listening and God was drawing him and later he came to faith in Christ.

07:52.486 --> 08:00.137
What I want to tell you about is that God gave us such a passion to see our other players on our team to come to Christ and other classmates.

08:00.457 --> 08:06.866
By the time I graduated from high school a year and a half later, of the 22 starters on that football team, 19,

08:08.034 --> 08:11.197
had either come to faith in Christ or were already believers when we started.

08:11.518 --> 08:12.699
It was in a public high school.

08:13.240 --> 08:18.385
God did an amazing work and it was undergirded in prayer.

08:19.226 --> 08:27.155
If we're gonna see God continue to do a great work in the communities and the towns here in North Georgia, everywhere that our church touches.

08:27.455 --> 08:31.900
And if we're gonna see God do a great work around the world, it is gonna be undergirded in prayer.

08:32.581 --> 08:37.106
And when we pray, we don't just pray for sick people to be healed.

08:37.442 --> 08:40.347
We also need to pray for lost people to be saved.

08:41.348 --> 08:43.472
And so I want us to talk this morning in this passage.

08:43.492 --> 08:46.116
I want to give you seven ways to pray evangelistically.

08:46.356 --> 08:48.920
If you haven't figured out already, there's seven points today.

08:49.061 --> 08:52.246
You may not have figured that out, but I want to tell you, there's seven points.

08:52.266 --> 08:52.987
Number one is this.

08:54.209 --> 08:56.032
We must pray at all times.

08:57.093 --> 09:00.799
At the beginning of verse 18, Paul says, pray at all times.

09:01.180 --> 09:02.482
Now let me just pause and say,

09:02.882 --> 09:11.153
If you haven't figured this out about me already, my points in my message, this is a few weeks ago, I hope that you leave going.

09:11.173 --> 09:12.655
That is exactly what the Bible said.

09:12.895 --> 09:15.599
My points are not always clever, but they're always clear.

09:15.619 --> 09:20.145
I try to make them crystal clear, and I try to draw them as much as possible straight from God's Word.

09:20.465 --> 09:23.449
Paul tells us pray at all times.

09:24.010 --> 09:26.994
Now, there are some people, man, they get up in the morning,

09:27.394 --> 09:31.761
I mean, their feet hit the floor, and they are talking and listening to God, and they're praying.

09:32.102 --> 09:36.990
Some people, even before they get out of bed, I mean, it's like they begin their day, and that's a great discipline.

09:37.010 --> 09:39.454
I mean, it's just a great way to start the day.

09:39.935 --> 09:45.564
Other people, they particularly, when they pause for the first meal of the day, all the meals, they take time to pray.

09:45.985 --> 09:49.911
Other people, if they get a big test at school, they are gonna stop and pray.

09:50.332 --> 09:54.098
Other people, big thing on the job, they're gonna pray about it.

09:54.274 --> 09:58.878
Others, you know, they encounter somebody and they get a situation, man, they will pause and pray.

09:59.719 --> 10:04.664
Others, by the time you get to bedtime, I mean, they are drifting off to sleep, talking, and listening to God.

10:04.924 --> 10:06.986
These are all awesome times to pray.

10:07.386 --> 10:12.792
Do you know the Apostle Paul tells us in another place, pray without ceasing or pray continually.

10:13.372 --> 10:17.997
It doesn't mean always hands folded, eyes closed, head bowed, praying.

10:18.337 --> 10:23.762
It means our conversation throughout the day is a prayer to God.

10:24.418 --> 10:26.280
A lot of listening, a lot talking.

10:26.941 --> 10:28.763
It's a conversation throughout the day.

10:29.163 --> 10:41.537
If you're gonna pray for lost people, if you're gonna pray for lost people to come to Christ, here's what you begin to see is that when God brings someone to mind, they may be lost and you pray for them.

10:42.098 --> 10:43.440
God, I don't know why I just thought about Him.

10:43.500 --> 10:49.186
I haven't thought about Him in years or God, I know I'm about to go to the grocery store or to work or whatever.

10:49.406 --> 10:52.690
Man, I'm gonna pray for Him or her to come to faith in Christ.

10:52.770 --> 10:58.419
Students, man, I pray for my classmates and my teachers and all these people to come to faith in Christ.

10:58.660 --> 11:00.964
So we pray at all times.

11:01.224 --> 11:04.009
In other words, there's never a bad time to pray.

11:04.570 --> 11:06.233
So you need to begin to have the mind set.

11:06.253 --> 11:09.418
I'm going to be in an attitude of prayer all the time.

11:09.438 --> 11:16.690
One thing that's very specific that's helped me, if this will help you or not, when I'm driving down the road, I have

11:17.314 --> 11:22.140
Man, I used to listen to music all the time, then I listen to talk radio, then I listen to sports radio.

11:22.661 --> 11:25.644
I have turned the radio off when I'm driving.

11:25.965 --> 11:32.793
Not just because, you know, whatever, but I mean, how many times every six minutes can you hear what the weather's gonna be?

11:34.575 --> 11:40.803
But the bottom line for me in my life, it's been a good discipline of solitude and prayer, just some driving down the road.

11:41.524 --> 11:46.610
And so I don't know what it is for you that you need to maybe adjust in your life so that

11:46.690 --> 11:52.838
The world's noise is not so busy in your ears, but the God's word and the Holy Spirit through prayer.

11:52.858 --> 11:54.339
So pray at all times.

11:54.620 --> 11:57.343
Point number two, pray in the spirit.

11:57.383 --> 12:01.228
Verse 18 also says, pray at all times in the spirit.

12:01.849 --> 12:05.693
What this means is pray in sync with the spirit.

12:05.713 --> 12:10.219
Pray in line with the spirit, which is always in line with God's word.

12:10.940 --> 12:14.644
The Holy Spirit is always in line with God's word.

12:15.265 --> 12:15.986
And so as you,

12:16.130 --> 12:22.517
saturate yourself by reading God's Word, you will learn to pray in line with the Spirit.

12:22.918 --> 12:33.389
So as you know, again, when God brings someone to mind that God doesn't want you to pray God's judgment on them, because that's, you know, Romans 12, that's up to the Lord to do.

12:33.469 --> 12:35.191
No, no, we're praying for salvation.

12:35.612 --> 12:37.294
We're praying God's blessings.

12:37.314 --> 12:41.438
We're praying that God would grow people's spirits if they already know Christ, and we're gonna get to some of these things.

12:41.819 --> 12:44.722
But we begin to realize that we pray at all times,

12:45.218 --> 12:48.623
But we pray in the spirit and what that also means is we're not just saying words.

12:50.045 --> 12:53.290
We're not just repeating something that is meaningless.

12:53.751 --> 12:59.359
No, no, praying in the spirit means man, I am right in sync with God and the Holy Spirit.

12:59.379 --> 13:02.464
So we pray at all times and we pray in the spirit.

13:02.484 --> 13:04.286
Here's the third thing I want to see that we pray.

13:04.687 --> 13:10.596
Not only do we pray at all times in the spirit, but thirdly, we pray for other believers.

13:11.157 --> 13:12.018
Pray for other believers.

13:12.118 --> 13:13.039
Paul writes it this way.

13:14.181 --> 13:14.802
He says,

13:15.682 --> 13:23.871
Pray it all times in the spirit with every prayer and request and stay alert with all perseverance and intercession for all the saints.

13:23.991 --> 13:33.060
And then the way he says in verse 19, pray also for me that the message baby given to me when I open my mouth to make it known with boldness and we'll stop there for a second.

13:33.981 --> 13:36.063
Pray for other believers.

13:36.404 --> 13:39.267
Now I know what you may say, you may say, I do that all the time.

13:39.747 --> 13:42.610
Anytime I hear for somebody that they're sick, I pray for them.

13:43.042 --> 13:46.467
Anytime I hear there's a financial crisis, I'll pray for them and it's a relationship issue.

13:46.547 --> 13:49.211
I will pray for them and pray all these things.

13:49.692 --> 13:54.178
But did you ever think that God may want you to pray for other believers?

13:54.298 --> 14:02.470
Paul, one of the greatest missionaries of angels we ever know, asked them, pray for him that he might be bold in sharing the gospel.

14:03.191 --> 14:05.715
How about you ask other believers to pray for you?

14:05.755 --> 14:07.558
And how about you?

14:07.598 --> 14:10.642
Many of you have these things called smartphones.

14:10.882 --> 14:13.627
And they have this feature on them called text messaging.

14:14.528 --> 14:22.041
And when you, or Instagram, or however you communicate with the world, when you send a message to someone else like that, how about you do this?

14:22.602 --> 14:23.203
Say, you know what?

14:23.544 --> 14:24.445
God brought you to mind.

14:25.287 --> 14:26.268
I know you love Jesus.

14:26.909 --> 14:30.235
I am praying for you today that you will be a witness for Christ.

14:31.177 --> 14:36.626
What would happen this week if we prayed for one another to be a bold witness for Christ?

14:36.898 --> 14:39.362
And then we let each other know that we're doing that.

14:39.622 --> 14:42.206
Man, how encouraging and how.

14:42.406 --> 14:47.294
I mean, in touch with the power of God that we are saying, I am praying and we are praying for one another.

14:47.654 --> 14:48.576
Paul asked for that.

14:48.836 --> 14:53.684
He says, praying for all an intercession for all the saints and pray for me.

14:54.905 --> 15:01.095
That group of guys that I'm talking about from our high school, these eight guys that started, man, we had each other's back.

15:01.115 --> 15:03.218
I mean, we were always holding each other accountable.

15:03.618 --> 15:07.403
to live for Christ and we were praying together and we were praying for one another.

15:07.663 --> 15:10.086
And so I'm asking you, who are you praying for?

15:10.146 --> 15:13.630
It may be the people in your community group, those may be the people that you know the best.

15:14.051 --> 15:17.255
Maybe people in your own family, men as you're scattered each and every day.

15:17.315 --> 15:24.945
Again, parents, you pray for your kids and you send them a text and say, okay, I know you can't read this because you're at school and you're not supposed to be on your phone.

15:24.965 --> 15:30.211
But whenever you see this, I'm praying for you that you'll be living for Jesus today.

15:30.812 --> 15:32.594
How encouraging is that?

15:33.410 --> 15:35.453
praying for other believers.

15:36.054 --> 15:39.840
Number four, praying for the lost to be drawn to Christ.

15:40.321 --> 15:43.046
I want to ask you to turn, if you will, to John chapter six.

15:44.007 --> 15:44.889
John chapter six.

15:47.413 --> 15:55.225
Because truly Jesus talks about the very fact that God is the one who draws people to faith in Jesus.

15:55.866 --> 15:57.108
It's God who draws them.

15:57.990 --> 16:00.594
Look at John chapter six, verse 44.

16:01.890 --> 16:05.656
John six verse 44 says, no one can come to me.

16:05.716 --> 16:06.878
This is Jesus speaking.

16:07.278 --> 16:15.130
No one can come to me unless a father who sent me draws him and I will raise him up on the last day.

16:15.170 --> 16:21.660
No one can come to me unless a father who sent me draws him and I will raise him up on the last day.

16:22.742 --> 16:26.167
It is God who draws people to faith in Christ.

16:26.588 --> 16:30.674
And so if we're gonna pray at all times in the spirit,

16:31.330 --> 16:39.861
then we are praying that the loss be drawn to Christ because we see in this passage, John 644, that it is God who draws people to faith in Christ.

16:40.222 --> 16:47.111
And so therefore we pray in line with God's word, by his spirit, asking God to draw people to faith in Christ.

16:47.731 --> 16:58.045
Now, speaking of drawing, so when I was a student pastor, I would encourage our students to take a piece of paper and to draw a sort of diagram.

16:58.365 --> 16:58.866
I said like,

16:59.266 --> 17:03.010
This is like your first period class, you know the piece of paper, your second period class, whatever.

17:03.691 --> 17:11.760
And on that piece of paper, draw boxes and those represent the desks in your room, in your classroom.

17:12.140 --> 17:18.307
Put your name where you sit and then put on the people's name because everybody sort of has assigned seats or regular seats, they sit in.

17:19.488 --> 17:22.151
You know these people, are you getting to know them throughout the semester?

17:23.032 --> 17:24.133
Find out if they're believers.

17:24.994 --> 17:28.498
If they're a believer, then point number three is you pray for them

17:28.642 --> 17:30.144
that they will be a witness for Christ.

17:31.106 --> 17:36.093
If they're not a believer yet, you're praying for them to be drawn to faith in Christ.

17:36.554 --> 17:42.743
What would happen if each of us had that kind of a chart or grid that we were thinking about the people all around us?

17:42.823 --> 17:48.271
I mean, folks, moms and dads, grandparents, what about your neighborhood or the people in your work?

17:48.731 --> 17:49.252
People in your work.

17:49.272 --> 17:52.156
I mean, you're thinking about your desk or you're thinking about the people you interact with.

17:52.597 --> 17:55.020
Maybe you're thinking about the organizational chart at your work.

17:55.421 --> 17:56.082
And then you're like,

17:56.258 --> 18:04.610
Hey, there's real people there, some of them are believers, some of them are not, some of them you don't know, you don't even know yet if they're a believer, but man, you're praying for them.

18:05.031 --> 18:18.291
And so what I'm asking you today, and you go listen, I'm asking you today, I'm gonna ask you to leave this place with specific names that God's lay on your heart that this week you're gonna be praying for.

18:19.593 --> 18:26.002
So I'm asking you even now to begin to think about and during the message, jot their name down if you're taking notes with a pen or pencil,

18:26.146 --> 18:33.493
If you're gonna get your phone and put a text note, whatever, send yourself a memo, write it down so that you won't forget.

18:33.533 --> 18:37.137
These are the people that God's laying on your heart to pray for.

18:38.198 --> 18:43.563
And when you begin to do that, you begin to see the people all around you that need Jesus.

18:43.583 --> 18:47.647
We're praying for the lost to be drawn to Christ.

18:47.948 --> 18:54.354
It is good to pray for all those things we mentioned before, for relationships to get mended, for financial,

18:54.498 --> 19:00.564
challenges to be met, for God to show up in big ways with all sorts of medical and health issues.

19:00.884 --> 19:05.989
But the most important thing we can pray for is for the lost to be saved.

19:06.009 --> 19:07.511
That they would come to faith in Christ.

19:07.531 --> 19:13.377
And so I'm asking you, as a church family, I'm asking us if we will pray like never before.

19:13.837 --> 19:22.706
My prayer is that even this week would be the greatest week of prayer we've ever had as Concord for the sake of the lost.

19:22.882 --> 19:25.645
And there's been some great weeks of prayer in this church.

19:26.006 --> 19:30.711
May we have another great week of prayer, maybe the greatest one ever, that people will come to faith in Christ.

19:31.252 --> 19:32.733
Pray for the loss to be drawn to Christ.

19:33.094 --> 19:33.975
Point number four is that.

19:34.015 --> 19:34.716
Point number five.

19:35.176 --> 19:38.460
Pray for open doors for the gospel.

19:39.401 --> 19:40.843
Pray for open doors for the gospel.

19:40.883 --> 19:46.549
Let me ask you to take your Bible and turn to Colossians chapter four and verse three.

19:47.310 --> 19:50.834
Pray for open doors for the gospel.

19:51.330 --> 20:08.569
Colossians four, verse three says, Paul writes, and again this is Apostle Paul, he says at the same time, pray also for us that God may open a door for us for the word, to speak the mystery of Christ for which I am in chains.

20:09.811 --> 20:10.672
Do you see it right there?

20:11.132 --> 20:15.717
Pray that God may open a door for us for the word, to speak the mystery of Christ.

20:17.139 --> 20:19.922
Paul is praying and saying God, open the door wide open.

20:20.482 --> 20:22.365
And let me see that the door is wide open.

20:23.207 --> 20:33.986
Pray again, praying all the time by the spirit or in the spirit, praying for the believers, praying for the loss to be drawn to Christ, people to be drawn to Christ.

20:34.006 --> 20:35.930
And now we're praying for open doors.

20:36.350 --> 20:36.952
Let me ask you this.

20:37.653 --> 20:39.997
Any of you got a new vehicle recently?

20:40.037 --> 20:42.001
I mean, may not be brand new, but it's new to you.

20:42.461 --> 20:42.802
Well,

20:43.138 --> 20:46.622
I drive a black truck and I love driving a black truck I have for years.

20:47.082 --> 20:51.587
Let's imagine for a moment that you used to drive a white sedan and now you drive a black truck.

20:52.688 --> 20:57.373
You will notice that you begin to see black trucks everywhere.

20:58.154 --> 21:01.738
You didn't realize there were so many black trucks on the road until you started driving one.

21:02.138 --> 21:11.028
It's just now your eyes are open and you notice what we're asking is in the same way God helped me to see the open doors all around for the gospel.

21:11.428 --> 21:13.010
There are open doors every day.

21:13.378 --> 21:16.462
And you pray and say, God, help me to pray it all times.

21:17.404 --> 21:19.607
In the spirit, praying for other believers.

21:20.328 --> 21:31.965
And man, if you're praying for other believer over there, and you're praying for the loss to come to Christ, God opens the door wide open as somebody just talks to you at work, at school, and you begin to realize this is an open door.

21:32.185 --> 21:33.667
It's an open door to serve someone.

21:33.968 --> 21:36.431
It's an open door to maybe invite someone to church.

21:36.491 --> 21:38.354
It's an open door to pray with someone.

21:38.882 --> 21:41.907
It's an open door, perhaps to even share the gospel.

21:41.947 --> 21:44.611
So we're praying, God, you open the doors.

21:44.991 --> 21:49.778
Paul encourages us in Colossians 4 that we pray for open doors.

21:50.119 --> 21:55.748
So the loss being drawn to Christ, and then the doors wide open, number six is this.

21:56.228 --> 21:58.832
Pray for boldness in sharing the gospel.

21:59.193 --> 22:02.197
If you will, go back to Ephesians chapter six, verse 19.

22:02.798 --> 22:04.961
Pray for boldness in sharing the gospel.

22:06.003 --> 22:07.986
Verse 19, he says, pray also for me,

22:08.514 --> 22:14.484
that the message may be given to me when I open my mouth to make known with boldness the mystery of the gospel.

22:15.165 --> 22:17.729
For this, I am an ambassador in chains.

22:18.410 --> 22:22.637
Pray that I might be bold enough to speak about it as I should.

22:23.598 --> 22:27.405
You know what many people would have prayed if they were in Paul's position?

22:28.927 --> 22:35.698
God, get me out of jail and then I'll be bold, right?

22:35.938 --> 22:38.964
Most people to pray, God, get me out of this circumstance and then I'll be bold.

22:39.625 --> 22:44.916
Paul knew that he was in the circumstances he was because God had allowed him to be there.

22:45.658 --> 22:49.485
He knew that he needed to be bold for the gospel and if it meant being in jail, he was going to do it.

22:50.106 --> 22:55.117
This may surprise you, I'm actually very grateful to God that the Apostle Paul went to jail.

22:56.860 --> 22:57.842
You say, Derek, that's sort of...

22:58.114 --> 22:59.415
messed up, sort of wicked.

23:00.256 --> 23:00.857
But here's why.

23:01.137 --> 23:06.082
The Apostle Paul was a traveling evangelist and missionary church planter.

23:06.602 --> 23:10.726
He was busy starting churches all throughout Roman Empire.

23:13.189 --> 23:20.316
Had he not been put in prison, he may not have ever paused long enough to write.

23:21.897 --> 23:26.962
But through his writing and God through the Holy Spirit inspired

23:27.106 --> 23:33.456
these things that he wrote down, we have many of the letters that we now know is a word of God.

23:34.437 --> 23:41.187
If Paul wouldn't have been put in prison, he would not, in my view, have taken time to write.

23:41.227 --> 23:49.520
So I'm grateful to God that Paul endured those circumstances, was a witness for Christ there, and then took the opportunity to write these things down.

23:50.381 --> 23:56.370
When Paul did, again, he didn't say, God, get me out of the circumstance, he said, God,

23:56.546 --> 23:57.387
Help me to be bold.

23:58.108 --> 23:59.550
Now, sure, there's wisdom.

23:59.911 --> 24:01.192
You're not going to be brash.

24:01.253 --> 24:04.056
You're not going to be the kind of person that's a bull in the china shop.

24:04.076 --> 24:09.624
You're not going to be a person who, through your delivering your mannerisms or just, you know, offensive and things like that.

24:10.165 --> 24:12.368
But boldness is saying Jesus is the answer.

24:13.109 --> 24:14.491
Jesus died for you on the cross.

24:14.892 --> 24:16.314
Jesus will forgive you of your sins.

24:16.674 --> 24:18.176
Jesus rose to the dead.

24:18.416 --> 24:20.059
Jesus can give you eternal life.

24:20.419 --> 24:22.582
Jesus calls people to salvation.

24:22.943 --> 24:25.266
We are unashamed of the gospel.

24:25.506 --> 24:27.068
It's a power of God and salvation.

24:27.128 --> 24:31.293
And so we pray for boldness in sharing the gospel.

24:32.335 --> 24:36.480
One of our missionaries served for many years with the International Mission Board.

24:36.520 --> 24:38.583
He goes by the name of Nick Ripken.

24:38.903 --> 24:41.807
He wrote a book called The Insanity of God.

24:42.227 --> 24:46.753
If you have not read this book, I highly recommend it, The Insanity of God.

24:47.314 --> 24:50.738
He was a missionary in Africa, in Somalia in particular.

24:50.818 --> 24:58.849
He's actually a missionary there during the period of time that the events that are chronicled in the movie Black Hawk Down took place.

24:58.869 --> 25:01.212
So that was when he was there as a missionary.

25:01.773 --> 25:08.162
And he talks about the extreme persecution that the Somalis in particular had to endure for the sake of the gospel.

25:08.662 --> 25:17.074
His own family went through lots of trials by being there, some very, very, very, very difficult to endure.

25:17.250 --> 25:20.013
He served in Somali for many years in his family.

25:20.033 --> 25:33.429
He literally traveled the world meeting persecuted believers and hearing from them and I mean in Russia and China and all sorts of nations hearing them and their stories of faith in Christ.

25:34.370 --> 25:44.402
And consistent themes just emerged and you'll read about them in the book but one of the things that wasn't there was God give me out of this persecution.

25:45.890 --> 25:51.156
A consistent theme is God help me to endure this persecution and help me to be bold for the gospel.

25:54.039 --> 25:54.480
Is that you?

25:55.261 --> 25:55.761
Is that me?

25:57.303 --> 26:04.211
Hey, we need to say God help me to be bold like Paul was for the gospel.

26:04.271 --> 26:07.294
He was an ambassador in chains, literally.

26:07.715 --> 26:09.877
Can you imagine being the Roman guard chained to Paul?

26:10.438 --> 26:11.559
What are you going to talk about today?

26:12.420 --> 26:14.002
Probably not talking about football.

26:14.466 --> 26:16.528
You're probably gonna be talking about Jesus all day long.

26:17.569 --> 26:19.171
And Paul was a witness for Christ.

26:19.231 --> 26:20.952
Pray for boldness since you're in the gospel.

26:20.992 --> 26:24.696
Number seven, literally pray for people to be saved.

26:25.156 --> 26:26.077
Pray for people to be saved.

26:26.097 --> 26:31.062
Romans 10, 13 says, those who call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

26:31.743 --> 26:34.725
So if you're praying all these things, now, let's think about it.

26:34.745 --> 26:36.587
We're gonna get them all on the board here in a second.

26:36.607 --> 26:38.769
So we pray at all times.

26:40.031 --> 26:43.634
So you're aware and you're thinking about God literally

26:44.098 --> 26:44.378
24-7.

26:44.739 --> 26:49.245
And when you're awake, when you're thinking about it, so we're praying at all times.

26:49.786 --> 26:51.108
We're praying in the Spirit.

26:51.428 --> 26:55.153
We're not just saying words, we're not just doing some mental gymnastics.

26:55.173 --> 26:58.939
No, no, we're praying in the Spirit in line with God's Word through His Holy Spirit.

26:59.559 --> 27:00.961
And we're praying for other believers.

27:02.163 --> 27:05.828
A lot of things in their lives, but we're praying also for them to be a witness for Christ.

27:06.729 --> 27:09.994
And then we're praying for the lost people to be drawn to Christ.

27:10.895 --> 27:12.978
We're praying for open doors for the gospel.

27:13.698 --> 27:18.063
And then we're praying, and we're praying God, give us boldness to share.

27:20.565 --> 27:24.350
Well, if you're praying all those things, let's get people across the finish line.

27:25.351 --> 27:27.173
Let's pray for them to come to Christ.

27:28.014 --> 27:33.860
Pray believing, because there's some people you say, I don't know, because think about this.

27:34.460 --> 27:36.703
You know some people and you say, man, they're a good person.

27:37.524 --> 27:38.405
They're a good person.

27:39.045 --> 27:40.767
Let me tell you, good people don't go to heaven.

27:41.909 --> 27:43.250
Say people go to heaven.

27:43.906 --> 27:46.650
because a good person's got a whole bunch of sin that needs to be forgiven.

27:47.892 --> 27:52.799
But then on the other hand, you got people who are just so lost that it's obvious to everyone.

27:53.220 --> 27:58.488
Now you might be tempted to go, I could pray for them, but they'll never get saved.

27:58.508 --> 28:08.262
I bet many of you, you could tell me testimony of somebody that you said, that person was so far from God, it seemed like everybody else had given up on them, but God didn't give up on them.

28:08.302 --> 28:11.026
Other people were praying for them, and now they are a believer.

28:11.507 --> 28:13.650
Nobody is too lost that God can't save them.

28:13.890 --> 28:15.311
He goes after the lost sheep.

28:15.612 --> 28:20.056
Hey, we need to pray for the lost to be saved.

28:20.136 --> 28:21.278
Pray for people to be saved.

28:21.298 --> 28:25.262
And so as we wrap it up today, let me ask you, who are the people?

28:26.203 --> 28:27.824
I told you a few minutes ago, I was gonna ask you this.

28:28.505 --> 28:29.366
Who are the people?

28:29.806 --> 28:31.408
I literally want you to write it.

28:31.428 --> 28:32.849
This is not like just my talking.

28:33.310 --> 28:34.551
I want you to write it down.

28:34.571 --> 28:41.458
I want you to text yourself, however you need to get a message to yourself to remember to resolve this week.

28:42.178 --> 28:43.159
that you will be praying.

28:43.239 --> 28:48.204
You'll be praying for other believers, as we already talked about, but you're gonna be praying for the loss to be saved.

28:48.704 --> 28:50.586
And then let that list grow.

28:50.646 --> 28:59.735
But I'm asking you this week to resolve every day as part of your time of prayer, that you would pray evangelistically.

29:00.296 --> 29:06.642
For other believers to be witness, for God opened doors, and for the loss to be saved as we share Christ.

29:07.082 --> 29:08.264
Can we bow together in prayer?

29:09.405 --> 29:10.706
So the invitation today,

29:11.394 --> 29:12.776
First of all, it's for believers.

29:14.919 --> 29:16.300
It's for believers to pray.

29:17.942 --> 29:20.986
You may want to come and pray here at the front.

29:21.968 --> 29:26.433
I'm actually gonna ask if, like if you're one of the leaders of our church, you say, I'm one of the leaders.

29:27.615 --> 29:33.642
Then when we stand and sing in just a moment, would you lead the way and just come here to the front?

29:34.724 --> 29:39.570
And just with the people God's place on your heart, would you just pause for a moment and pray?

29:39.810 --> 29:41.633
pray for them to come to know Christ.

29:42.053 --> 29:45.779
Pray for the believers that you're going to be praying for, that there'll be a witness for Christ.

29:45.799 --> 29:57.457
So in a moment when we stand, I know on many Sundays we don't have a lot of movement necessarily, but I pray that today people would step out.

29:57.477 --> 30:01.162
If you're a leader of our church, I'm just asking you to come and just take a moment and pray at the front.

30:03.385 --> 30:07.371
There are others who are here and you need to give your life to Christ.

30:08.233 --> 30:09.074
You realize

30:09.858 --> 30:13.041
that Jesus died for you on the cross to pay the penalty for your sin.

30:13.562 --> 30:15.424
And He rose from the dead and you believed that.

30:16.325 --> 30:18.887
And you're ready to turn away from your sin and trust in Christ.

30:20.249 --> 30:22.992
And maybe even right now you'd pray and say, Jesus saved me.

30:23.993 --> 30:25.114
I commit my life to you.

30:26.876 --> 30:36.626
Hey, if you need to give your life to Christ today, if you need to be saved, when we stand and others are coming to pray, staff and some are all our leaders, hey,

30:37.186 --> 30:46.036
I'm gonna ask you if you're giving your life to Christ today to come to one of us who's standing here at the front and just say to me and one of other pastors and leaders, today I'm giving my life to Christ.

30:46.716 --> 30:53.444
There may be others who you say, I've been saved but I've never been baptized.

30:54.144 --> 30:58.890
Let us help you get that set up soon, come and let us know that and we will help you with that.

31:00.351 --> 31:06.738
A third may be, as we've had recently in some of our services, people coming forward and just saying,

31:07.522 --> 31:10.866
Today, man, this is the church family I need to be a member of.

31:11.546 --> 31:13.248
I need to be all in.

31:13.829 --> 31:20.436
And so maybe you, when we stand in a moment, maybe you want to come to me one of the leaders and say, pastors and leaders and say, I want to be a member.

31:20.456 --> 31:25.081
So again, the invitation, first of all, is for believers to come to the front.

31:25.522 --> 31:29.466
Our leaders in particular, but anybody can come from the youngest of the oldest, and let's pray.

31:29.646 --> 31:31.288
Let's make this be a place of prayer.

31:32.329 --> 31:36.914
And then also, again, for those who need to be saved, baptized.

31:36.994 --> 31:39.379
soon, or those who want to join the church.

31:39.479 --> 31:42.306
I want to pray, and in Muaystand, I'm inviting you to come.

31:42.646 --> 31:45.112
Lord Jesus, thank you for your love for us, thank you for your word.

31:45.693 --> 31:49.521
I pray that you'd help us each to respond now as your cons to respond.

31:49.582 --> 31:57.138
Some for prayer, evangelism, evangelistic prayer, some for salvation, some for baptism,

31:57.506 --> 31:59.734
It's some for church membership as your leadness.

31:59.754 --> 32:02.001
God help us each to be obedient to what you're calling us to do.

32:02.383 --> 32:03.446
In Jesus' name we pray.

32:03.787 --> 32:04.088
Amen.

32:04.430 --> 32:04.971
Please stand.

32:05.072 --> 32:06.095
Leaders, would you lead the way?

32:06.236 --> 32:08.082
Let's pray and everyone else you come.

